==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tighten
<hw>Tight"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Tightened</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Tightening</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To draw tighter; to
straiten; to make more close in any manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Just where I please, with <qex>tightened</qex> rein⟦br⟧
I'll urge thee round the dusty plain.</q>
<rj><qau>Fawkes.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Tightening pulley</b></col> <fld>(Mach.)</fld>, <cd>a
pulley which rests, or is forced, against a driving belt to tighten
it.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tightener</ent>⟦br⟧
